Bean Class vs POJO Class
-------------------------
POJO class (Plain Old Java Object) : Pojo class does not follow any special restrictions other than those provided by java language specification.

Restrictions includes : 
1. Pojo class can implements Serializable interface.
2. It can contains default constructor or parameterized constructor
3. Data members can be public , private, protected or default
4. Member functions can be can be public , private, protected or default

Bean Class : Bean class also follows special restrictions other than those provided by java language specification.

Restrictions includes : 
1. Bean class must needs to implements Serializable interface.
2. It must contains default constructor
3. Data members must be private
4. Member functions must be public
